com.burstly.lib.component
Interface IBurstlyAdaptorListener

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractAdaptor.AdaptorListenerWrapper, AdaptorListener, BurstlyAdaptorListenerWrapper
public interface IBurstlyAdaptorListener

This interface should be used by third party SDK in order to integrate into Burstly SDK. For example if your network is MyBestNetwork you can use "mybest" as a networkName.
Note: each of these methods is called in UI thread.

Version:
1.13

Nested Class Summary
static class IBurstlyAdaptorListener.FullscreenInfo

Method Detail

failedToLoad

void failedToLoad(String networkName,
                  boolean isInterstitial,
                  String causeOfFailure)
Should be called when an ad request fails to get a new ad.

Parameters:
networkName - String loaded network name. Short name of your network (ex. "mybest")
isInterstitial - boolean defines that current failed ad was interstitial
causeOfFailure - String short cause of failure fetching ad

didLoad

void didLoad(String networkName,
             boolean isInterstitial)
Should be called when a new ad has been received and is about to be displayed.
This method has to be invoked AFTER ad has been fully configured and is ready to be shown.

Parameters:
networkName - String loaded network name. Short name of your network (ex. "mybest").
isInterstitial - boolean defines that current ad is interstitial

dismissedFullscreen

void dismissedFullscreen(IBurstlyAdaptorListener.FullscreenInfo info)
Must be called when a fullscreen advertise has been dismissed.

Parameters:
info - IBurstlyAdaptorListener.FullscreenInfo dismissed fullscreen info

shownFullscreen

void shownFullscreen(IBurstlyAdaptorListener.FullscreenInfo info)

Parameters:
info - IBurstlyAdaptorListener.FullscreenInfo loaded fullscreen info

adWasClicked

void adWasClicked(String networkName,
